  title           = {{A pan-European river and catchment database}},
  year            = {2007},
  isbn            = {9789279069413},
  abstract        = {Digital data on river networks, lakes and drainage basins (catchments)$\backslash$nare an important pre-requisite for modelling hydrological processes,$\backslash$nincluding the analysis of pressures and their impact on water resources.$\backslash$nDatasets covering extensive areas such as the European continent$\backslash$nare especially important for mapping and monitoring activities of$\backslash$nEuropean institutions. The European Water Framework directive, for$\backslash$nexample, explicitly asks for the setup of Geographical Information$\backslash$nSystems including detailed layers of water bodies (rivers, lakes,$\backslash$nwetlands) and their drainage basins, while European Environment Agency$\backslash$n(EEA) requires adequate river and catchment data for monitoring the$\backslash$nstatus and trends of water resources over the entire pan-European$\backslash$ncontinent.$\backslash$n$\backslash$nThe Catchment Characterisation and Modelling (CCM) activity of the$\backslash$nEuropean Commissions' Joint Research Centre has developed advanced$\backslash$nmethodologies to derive adequate layers from digital elevation data$\backslash$nand ancillary information. Drainage density has been modelled through$\backslash$nlandscape typology and lakes have been considered during river mapping.$\backslash$nFinally, the database was enriched with a set of attributes describing$\backslash$nimportant characteristics of catchments and river segments.$\backslash$n$\backslash$nThe resulting database covers the entire pan-European continent from$\backslash$nthe Atlantic to the Urals and from the Mediterranean to northern$\backslash$nScandinavia, including the Antlantic islands and Turkey. The use$\backslash$nof homogeneous input data and their analysis with the same methodology$\backslash$nensures data with comparable and well documented characteristics$\backslash$n(e.g. level of detail, geometric quality, attributes) over the entire$\backslash$narea.$\backslash$n$\backslash$nThis report details the background for developing this database, describes$\backslash$nthe methodology implemented, and discusses the strengths and limitations$\backslash$nof the approach. It is intended to inform decision makers, scientists$\backslash$nand technicians involved in water-related issues about the main characteristics$\backslash$nof this product as well as on its potential for different applications.},
